header.gameNote: CONTINENTAL TIRE LAS VEGAS CLASSIC AT LAS VEGAS

article.headline: Saint Mary's (Cal) 77, Missouri St. 61
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Brad Waldow and Matthew Dellavedova scored 17 points each to lead Saint Mary's to a 77-61 win over Missouri State in the Las Vegas Classic on Friday night. Stephen Holt added 16 points and Jorden Page 10 for the Gaels (11-2). Rob Jones had seven points and 10 rebounds, and Dellavedova dished out eight assists. Caleb Patterson scored 18 points and Jarmar Gulley 14 for the Bears (7-5). Kyle Weems added 11 points and seven rebounds. Saint Mary's went ahead 38-36 on Waldow's three-point play with 17:56 left. It upped the lead to 44-36 with consecutive 3-pointers by Holt and Dellavedova, and Missouri State got no closer than six the rest of the game. The Gaels led 33-29 at halftime.
